definitions.definition: In or to an elevated position.
examples: How high above land did you fly?
The desks were piled high with magazines.

definitions.definition: In or at a great value .
examples: Costs have grown higher this year again.

definitions.definition: At a pitch of great frequency .
examples: I certainly can't sing that high .

main_definition: In or to an elevated position.
secondary_definitions: In or at a great value .
